    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Right Bank and Left Bank Merlot?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Right Bank Bordeaux Merlots (Pomerol, Saint-Émilion) are typically more opulent and fruit-forward, with clay-limestone soils producing wines with silky tannins and rich plum flavors. Left Bank Merlots serve as blending partners to Cabernet Sauvignon in gravelly soils, creating more structured wines with herbaceous notes and firmer tannins that require longer aging.</p>
